(3, 'THE CEW BEAUTY AWARDS EDIT HAS LANDED!', '01-CEW-AWARDS-COLLECTION3412.jpg', '<p><strong>Eylure Faux Mink PROMAGENTIC</strong> On a night out, I feel naked if I&rsquo;m without a strong lash. Eylure&rsquo;s PROMAGENTIC Eyeliner and Lash System delivers the easiest lash application I&rsquo;ve ever encountered. As I have small eyes, I find the 3/4 length lash works best for me &ndash; adding fullness to the ends in perfect measure. Better yet, they&rsquo;re long-lasting and reusable for up to 15 wears per lash. Iconic London Prep, Set, Glow I couldn&rsquo;t make my selections without bringing home the glow. Rght? This hydrating mist contains light reflecting properties and leaves my skin with that coveted ICONIC glow. I like to spritz liberally after applying my makeup to set it all in place, but it&rsquo;s also nice on bare skin for a healthy, radiant look. Ciat&eacute; Watermelon Burst Hydrating Eye Patches Oh, I do love a novel skincare product, which is why Ciat&eacute; made the cut in my edit. Perfect for refreshing under the eyes, these skin superstars not only look cute, the brightening watermelon extract combined with niacinamide and the brand&rsquo;s vitamin complex helps to restore, revitalise and reduce the appearance of fine lines. I&rsquo;m approaching 30 so I&rsquo;ll take all that I can get. Color Wow Dream Filter I&rsquo;m not usually one to select haircare products, but Color Wow has changed that entirely. This breakthrough pre-shampoo treatment filters out minerals typically found in hard water (which London is cursed with) to prevent the fading of hair colour. It&rsquo;s ideal for my purple ends! Face Halo I will never miss an opportunity to add to my Face Halo stash &ndash; I&rsquo;ve built quite the collection! These stylish dual-sided pads are a more eco-friendly alternative to ordinary cotton pads because they&rsquo;re reusable and can be popped in the washing machine. Face Halo pads are great for removing my makeup and only require water, however I like to add a little bit of cleanser when a deeper clean is desired. Paula&rsquo;s Choice 10% Azelaic Acid Booster It&rsquo;s been no secret that my skin has been TERRIBLE as of late. In fact, until I discovered Paula&rsquo;s Choice&rsquo;s Azelaic Acid, I was at my wits end. This product has quite literally transformed my skin in a mere few weeks; reducing breakouts and diminishing the red marks that past spots had left behind. It&rsquo;s also the perfect alternative for those sensitive to benzoyl peroxide. CEW-TEAM-PICKS-HARRI Elemis-Pro-Collagen Marine Cream One of those products that actually works. When it comes to premium skincare, Elemis is always my go-to &ndash; it works so well under makeup too. Face Halo Body Face Halo products are so innovative. The supersized version for body works to exfoliate skin to perfection &ndash; ideal for pre fake tan! PRAI Ageless Throat &amp; D&eacute;colletage Night Creme This is such a luxury product to have among your beauty stash. It left my skin feeling intensely hydrated when I woke up &ndash; I love it. Scientia Dawn Elixir. I love trying new face oils and this didn&rsquo;t disappoint. Sinking into my skin effortless, it made my complexion look so much brighter and clearer. Code8 5Secs Express Lip &amp; Cheek Colour Carmen This is such a versatile product and works on both cheeks and lips. It&rsquo;s perfect for on the go so I&rsquo;ve popped it in my handbag for on-the-go top ups! Omorovicza Queen of Hungary Mist I&rsquo;ve been using this mist for years, it&rsquo;s the ultimate in luxury skincare and I&rsquo;ve gone through countless bottles &ndash; it really does work to refresh the skin at any stage of your routine. Sukin Rosehip Nourishing Cream Cleanser I have only recently discovered the power of cream cleansers, and this Sukin one is to die for! My skin feels clean, but never stripped after using it. Yadah Brightening Jelly Mask You can&rsquo;t go wrong with a sheet mask. I especially love a sheet mask with brightening qualities and the super fun packaging is an added bonus! Ark Skincare Advanced Action Plumping Lip Cream Though I am not unhappy with my lips, this lip cream from Ark Skincare has been great at keeping my lips soft and supple all winter. The added plumpness is a major confidence boost. Douvall&rsquo;s Skin High Argan &amp; Cannabis Oil You&rsquo;ve gotta love a CBD product, especially one that is vegan and organic! The Douvall&rsquo;s CBD oil has been a great addition to my night-time routine. I also rub any excess onto my tattoo for extra nourishment! Earth Kind Shampoo Bar I&rsquo;ve decided that my scent for 2020 is going to be bergamot. This shampoo bar smells so lush. The bar has also been a great addition to my gym bag. No more heavy bottles for me! SGX The Do-It-All 3-In-1 Dry Texture Spray I do my best to not wash my hair everyday, but for those in between days, I need a good dry shampoo. The SGX 3-in-1 keeps my hair looking fresh, and also keeps all the pesky fly aways at bay.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Sint natus, magnam illo cum fuga deserunt voluptas atque nostrum incidunt! Delectus culpa ipsa nobis quas ducimus ea, soluta eaque doloremque ullam.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Doloremque expedita repellat quasi culpa officiis inventore qui distinctio quia amet mollitia illum nesciunt quos eos tempore quaerat, necessitatibus, aut dolores et rem laboriosam. Ad commodi voluptates veniam doloremque libero!</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Numquam ad, quod nihil dignissimos repellat quisquam iusto! Illo quia blanditiis, sint magnam laborum fugiat, amet eveniet totam, nostrum laboriosam maiores quae velit perferendis quasi voluptate voluptatibus neque. Maxime, est.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Debitis ea error fugit, deserunt numquam commodi cupiditate consequatur distinctio nesciunt sapiente natus earum quibusdam ratione dolor fugiat, soluta hic blanditiis enim, ipsum inventore voluptate placeat quaerat nulla impedit officia.</div>\